      <bioghist id="aspace_bf1810bafd25932f04bd15da48d2d2fc">
         <head>LeGrand Cannon</head>
         <p>LeGrand Cannon Jr. (1899-1979, Yale College 1920), American novelist, author of <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
               <part>Look to the Mountain</part>
            </title>.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_1de57325522db1ea5b10a05ec98ec3a5">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The collection consists of writings and correspondence by or relating to the American novelist LeGrand Cannon. Writings consist of autograph manuscript and typescript drafts of Look to the mountain, Come home at even (also including proofs), and These are some stories about old George Brown. Correspondents include C. Beecher Hogan, Stephan Stearns, and Donald Wing.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_1ab06a83f42d9af80d5671ac79536bb2">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Organized into two series: I. Writings, circa 1943-circa1979. II. Correspondence, 1938-1942.</p>  
      </arrangement>
